%% Training Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Client
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Training Operator Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS (self-signed)
    participant Controller as Training Operator Controller
    participant DNS as CoreDNS<br/>53/UDP
    participant InitC as PyTorch Init Container
    participant Workers as Training Worker Pods<br/>(via Headless Service)
    participant Prom as Prometheus<br/>(openshift-monitoring)

    Note over User,Workers: Flow 1: Training Job Submission and Execution

    User->>K8sAPI: POST PyTorchJob/TFJob/etc CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token/Certificate
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-kubeflow-org-v1-*<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS (self-signed)<br/>Auth: API Server TLS Client Cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation Response (admit/deny)
    K8sAPI-->>User: CR Created/Rejected

    Note over Controller: Reconciliation Loop
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch for training job CRs<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: CR Event (Added/Modified)

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Pods (master + workers)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Headless Service<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicy (PyTorch only)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create HPA (elastic PyTorch only)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create PodGroup (gang sched, optional)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over InitC,DNS: Flow 3: PyTorch Init Container DNS Check

    InitC->>DNS: Resolve master pod address<br/>53/UDP DNS plaintext
    DNS-->>InitC: Master pod IP via Headless Service

    Note over Workers: Flow: Distributed Training Communication
    Workers->>Workers: Inter-worker communication<br/>Framework-specific ports/TCP<br/>plaintext, no auth

    Note over Prom,Controller: Flow 2: Metrics Collection

    Prom->>Controller: GET /metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP plaintext<br/>Auth: None (via PodMonitor)
    Controller-->>Prom: Prometheus metrics
